.TH GIT\-ISSUE\-STATE 1 "2026-02-07" "git-issue 0.5.0" "Git Issue Manual"
.SH NAME
git\-issue\-state \- change the state of an issue
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git issue state
.I <issue-id>
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Change the state of an issue.
The state change is recorded as a new commit with a
.B State:
trailer.
Additional metadata such as fixing commit, release version,
and close reason can be attached.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-open
Set the state to
.BR open .
.TP
.B \-\-close
Set the state to
.BR closed .
.TP
.BI \-\-state " " <value>
Set the state to a custom value.
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-message " " \fI<text>\fR
Add a message with the state change.
.TP
.BI \-\-fixed\-by " " <sha>
Record the commit SHA that fixes this issue.
Stored as a
.B Fixed\-By:
trailer.
.TP
.BI \-\-release " " <version>
Record the release version.
Stored as a
.B Release:
trailer.
.TP
.BI \-\-reason " " <reason>
Reason for closing:
.BR duplicate ", " wontfix ", " invalid ", " completed .
Stored as a
.B Reason:
trailer.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show usage information.
.SH EXAMPLES
Close an issue:
.RS
.nf
$ git issue state a1b2c3d --close
.fi
.RE
.PP
Close with details:
.RS
.nf
$ git issue state a1b2c3d --close \\
    --fixed-by abc1234 --release v1.2.0 \\
    --reason completed -m "Verified in staging"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Reopen an issue:
.RS
.nf
$ git issue state a1b2c3d --open -m "Regression found"
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git\-issue (1),
.BR git\-issue\-edit (1),
.BR git\-issue\-show (1)
